            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-10-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-10-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="684" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d684">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00116 PW/10–545</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Acting Political Adviser in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Atcheson</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="37" xml:id="d684fn1">Mr. Atcheson was Acting Political
                        Adviser to the Supreme Commander, Allied Powers, Japan, with personal rank
                        of Minister.</note>
                    <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-10-05">October 5,
                            1945</date>.<lb/>[Received October 22.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to enclose a copy of a war
                    criminals list and an amendment list dated September 28 and October 2
                        respectively.<note n="38" xml:id="d684fn2">Neither printed; the lists
                        contained 56 persons of several nationalities.</note> These lists were
                    furnished to us by General MacArthur’s headquarters. Copies of further lists
                    will be forwarded as they become available.<note n="39" xml:id="d684fn3">A
                        supplemental list containing 15 additional names was enclosed with despatch
                        12, October 11, 1945 (740.00116 P.W./10–1145).</note>
                </p>
                <p>Respectfully yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">George Atcheson, Jr.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
